<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1920-11-18T15:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1920-11-18T15:00:00-05:00" n="891" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d891">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">661.4116/108: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Great Britain</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Davis</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                    State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Extract—Paraphrase]</seg></opener>
                            <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1920-11-18T20:00:00+00:00"><hi rend="italic">November
                                            18, 1920—8 p.m.</hi></date><lb/>[Received November
                                    18—7:35 p.m.]</dateline></opener>
                            <p>1633. It was decided by the Cabinet this morning to proceed with the
                                project for trade with Soviet Russia. For that purpose the Cabinet
                                gave its approval to the resumption of trade negotiations with
                                Krassin immediately.</p>
                            <p rend="center">. . . . . . . . . . . . . .</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Davis</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>